Exaggerate: The claim that the candidate did not take any "corporate PAC money" is exaggerated because the expert found evidence that the candidate did receive contributions from PACs, some of which were funded by corporations.
Lack enough support: The claim lacks enough support because the expert provides evidence from the Federal Election Commission and statements from researchers to contradict it.
